# rclone filter rules for SharePoint sync.
#
# Order matters — first match wins. Lines starting with `-` exclude;
# lines starting with `+` include; `**` matches anything recursively.
# Anything not matched by an exclude rule is included by default.
#
# Used by /sharepoint-sync (both push and pull):
#   rclone copy <src> <dst> --update --filter-from .rclone-filter
#
# Principle: SharePoint mirrors everything EXCEPT code, build artefacts,
# tooling internals, and secrets. Agent infrastructure (CLAUDE.md,
# glossary.md, docs/, .tickets/, analysis/) DOES sync — it's a feature.

# === Code (lives in git only, not SharePoint) ===
- /src/**
- /scripts/**

# === Generated artefacts (regeneratable from code) ===
- /output/**

# === Build & runtime ===
- /.venv/**
- /venv/**
- /.idea/**
- /.vscode/**
- __pycache__/**
- *.pyc
- *.pyo
- *.egg-info/**
- /build/**
- /dist/**

# === Git internals ===
- /.git/**
- /.gitignore

# === Agent install (symlinks would break on remote) ===
# Match at any depth — Claude state files can appear inside data dirs
# during ad-hoc edits (and have done so in practice on shared SharePoint folders).
- /.claude/**
- **/.claude/**

# === Register entry (DOES sync) ===
# .register/entry.yaml is per-project register data, swept by the
# research-overseer. Must sync to SharePoint so another agent picking
# up the SharePoint folder reads the same canonical entry. No filter
# rule needed (we exclude only specific dot dirs; .register/ is
# included by default). Comment is for documentation only.

# === Secrets and local config ===
- /.env
- /.env.*
- /.rclone-filter

# === Build metadata (code-side) ===
- /pyproject.toml
- /poetry.lock
- /uv.lock
- /requirements*.txt

# === OS junk ===
- .DS_Store
- Thumbs.db
